data.name: metroLabel7.Text
data.value:
Creating a new plan:
1) To create a new plan, you should first create a new file either through clicking the button "NEW" on the home screen or through File>new on the menu bar.
2) Now create a task, give it a name and some additional information if necessary. set it's date, make sure That the end date is somewhere in the future.
3) To edit your tasks, press the "INFO" button underneath the corresponding progressbar located on the left hand side. Here, you can change values. Don't forget to save!
4) To save your plans, press 'ctrl + S' or save from File>save as. Locate a safe place to save your .plan file, Give it a meaningful name.
Opening tasks:
1) To open a task, you can do it though pressing the "OPEN" button located on the home screen or through File>open.
2) You can also load your recent files from the home screen.

data.value:
PLANNER NEWS NOT LOADING - If the news isn't loading, it may be due to a number of reasons, which includes: no internet connection, the news source is down or the program is broken. The most common issue is if your internet connection is down, but if you think this program is encountering the other two issues, report your issue on the 'bug report' channel in the Discord server. (see About)
CANNOT LOCATE FILE TO LOAD - Check if you have misplaced your file. The file extension associated with your file is '.plan'.
RECENT PANEL NOT UPDATING WITH TASKS OPENED OR CREATED: Issues with files from older versions of planner may not be compatible with newer versions, otherwise, delete this data file through: Options>General settings.
AUTOSAVE NOT WORKING: Check if you have turned it on through: Options>General settings, otherwise, make sure that you have already saved your project into any directory.

data.name: metroLabel8.Text
data.value:
Autosave - automatically saves your work periodically or every time changes are made, this function comes into effect once you have already saved your work.
Recent data location - change the folder directory in which the 'recent' data file is located in.
Clear/reset recent data - clears data in case of buggy software issues or malfunction.
Disable/enable update notifications - whether you are subscribed for software updates or not.
Enable/disable splash screen - determines whether the splashscreen is visible on start.
Autoscroll on mouse hover - When enabled, task information will automatically scroll on mouse hover.
Show saved status - sets the format for how the saved status is presented.
